<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-3-2-solve-ineq">
    <statement>
        <p>
            In <xref ref="act-3-2-setup-ineq" text="type-global" />, we set up the inequality
            <me>
                3{,}900 + 4.2B \leq 18{,}000
            </me>
            to express the fact that a truck must obey the state highway weight limit of 18,000 pounds. 
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    Solve this inequality by applying the <xref ref="assemblage-shoes-and-socks" text="title"/>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Another way we could have set up this inequality is 
                    <me>18{,}000 \geq 3{,}900 + 4.2B</me>
                    Explain why this inequality expresses the same fact about trucks obeying the weight limit.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Try solving this version of the inequality. Do you get the same result?
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</activity>